# Fork the Repository:

Fork this sample repository to your GitHub account.
Clone the Repository:

Clone the forked repository to your local machine using the git clone command.
Create a Branch:

Create a new branch named my-feature.
Make Changes:

In the project directory, create a new file named my-info.txt.
Add a few lines introducing yourself to my-info.txt.
Commit Changes:

Commit your changes with a meaningful commit message.
Push Changes:

Push the changes to your forked repository on GitHub.
Create a Pull Request:

Navigate to the original repository.
Create a pull request from your my-feature branch to the original repository's main branch.
Write a Comment:

Write a comment on the pull request describing the changes you made.
Merge Pull Request:

Merge the pull request into the main branch.
Fetch Changes:

Fetch the changes from the original repository to your local machine.
Final Submission:

Submit a comment on the assignment issue indicating that you have completed the tasks.
Grading:

20 points: Forked repository.
20 points: Cloned repository locally.
20 points: Created and switched to my-feature branch.
20 points: Added my-info.txt with a self-introduction.
20 points: Created a pull request and merged changes.
